---
import ChecklistDownloadGate from "@/components/forms/ChecklistDownloadGate";
import BasicLayout from "@/layouts/BasicLayout.astro";
---

<BasicLayout
  title="Due Diligence Checklist | Multi-Family USA"
  description="Multifamily due diligence checklist for US 5+ unit acquisitions and refinances—legal, operating, physical, lease, and lender documentation."
  crumbs={[
    { label: "Home", href: "/" },
    { label: "Checklists", href: "/checklists" },
    { label: "Due diligence checklist", href: "/checklists/due-diligence-checklist" },
  ]}
>
  <h1>Multifamily Due Diligence Checklist</h1>
  <p>
    Practical diligence framework for US commercial multifamily transactions with 5+
    units. Use this checklist to keep legal, financial, and operational workstreams
    aligned from term sheet through closing.
  </p>

  <h2>1) Financial diligence</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Reconcile trailing 12-month operating statements and rent roll totals.</li>
    <li>Build in-place and stabilized NOI bridges with support for each adjustment.</li>
    <li>Stress test occupancy, concessions, bad debt, and expense inflation.</li>
    <li>Validate debt sizing under DSCR, debt yield, and leverage constraints.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2) Lease and tenant diligence</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Audit lease terms, concessions, expiration clustering, and delinquency patterns.</li>
    <li>Confirm occupancy reporting methodology and unit-status definitions.</li>
    <li>Review tenant concentration and exposure to nonrecurring occupancy drivers.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3) Physical and capex diligence</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Complete PCA and relevant environmental reports required by lenders.</li>
    <li>Map immediate-life-safety needs versus strategic value-add improvements.</li>
    <li>Align capex sequencing with loan covenants, reserves, and lease-up timing.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4) Legal and entity diligence</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Verify borrowing entity formation documents and ownership structure.</li>
    <li>Confirm guarantor framework, authority documents, and signature readiness.</li>
    <li>Review title, survey, zoning, and litigation matters before loan-doc drafting.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5) Debt execution and closing controls</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Track lender conditions with owner-level due dates and document status.</li>
    <li>Confirm reserve requirements, escrows, and cash-management mechanics.</li>
    <li>Verify extension tests and refinance assumptions for transitional strategies.</li>
    <li>Prepare post-close reporting templates before funding.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How sponsors should implement this checklist</h2>
  <p>
    Assign one transaction owner to manage dependencies across legal counsel, lender
    counsel, third-party vendors, property management, and accounting. Weekly checkpoint
    calls with updated owner-level action lists usually reduce avoidable timeline slips.
  </p>

  <ChecklistDownloadGate
    client:load
    checklistId="due-diligence-checklist"
    checklistTitle="Multifamily Due Diligence Checklist"
    lang="en"
  />

  <p>
    If you want deal-specific execution feedback, submit your package through the
    <a href="/deal-review">free deal review</a>.
  </p>
</BasicLayout>
